Arizona Silver Corpsaid diamond drilling on its Burro Creek Mine Property, located65 miles southeast of Kingman, Ariz., has begun.    The company said a report indicated that the Burro Creekproject area which covers 800 acres, could have potentialreserves of three to four mln tons of gold and silvermineralization.    Drill sites have been established and a diamond drillingprogram consisting of an initial 5,000 feet of drilling beganOctober 13, the company said. Reuter&#3;